label.value: Immigrant From High Tuberculosis Prevalent Area

value.value: An individual that has migrated from a country with a high occurrence of tuberculosis.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to immune system findings.
A setting outside the clinic or a comparable health care facility, e.g., a doctor's office, the subject's home or workplace, a school, a public park, or a restaurant.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to integumentary system findings.

label.value: Junctional Premature Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of an ectopic impulse originating in the AV junction presenting as a QRS complex of supraventricular origin which is not preceded by a P wave. (CDISC)

label.value: Late R Wave Transition by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding where the amplitude of the R wave does not become greater than the amplitude of the S wave until an unusually late point in the precordial leads, usually in leads V4 to V6. (CDISC)
A bulge or ballooning in the wall of the left ventricle of the heart.

label.value: Left Ventricular Hypertrophy with Strain by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding suggestive of a hypertrophied left ventricle, characterized by large QRS amplitudes, ST depression and T wave inversion. (CDISC)

A technique in which polymerase chain reaction is used to amplify specific nucleic acid sequences in a biospecimen. The product of this reaction is then applied to a nitrocellulose test strip containing complementary DNA probes.
An individual that resided in a camp for those displaced from their homeland.

label.value: Log10 Colony Forming Units per Gram

value.value: A logarithmic-scale (base 10) unit for measuring colony forming units per unit of mass equal to one gram.

label.value: Log10 Colony Forming Units per Milliliter

value.value: A logarithmic-scale (base 10) unit for measuring colony forming units per unit of volume equal to one milliliter.

An individual that lives at a healthcare facility that provides rehabilitative, restorative, and/or ongoing skilled nursing care to patients or residents in need of assistance with activities of daily living.

A type of nucleic acid amplification test in which sample DNA is exposed to a single temperature in the presence of multiple sets of primers and a polymerase with replication and high strand displacement activity. This test negates the need for thermal cyclers and may be a low cost alternative to PCR.
An individual that has had limited exposure to an individual with tuberculosis and has a low probability of having had a recent infection.
The medication is no longer held or possessed by the subject and is incapable of being recovered or regained.
Medications that were lost because they were put in the wrong place.
An individual that has tested negative for pulmonary, laryngeal, or pleural tuberculosis but has had a non-cavitary chest x-ray that is consistent with tuberculosis.
An indication that a person is part of a population group that has a greater chance of contracting a disease or disorder.
A qualification that describes the degree of certainty of the correctness of a microbial identification test result.
A method for growing microorganisms in liquid culture media.
A method for growing microorganisms in solid culture media.
An individual who moves from one location to another location within or outside of their homeland for work.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to morphology findings.

label.value: Multifocal Atrial Premature Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of premature atrial complexes which have 2 or more distinct morphologies, suggesting origin at more than one atrial site. (CDISC)

label.value: Multifocal Ventricular Premature Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of premature ventricular complexes which have two or more distinct morphologies, suggesting origin at more than one ventricular site. (CDISC)

label.value: Musculoskeletal Findings, Connective and Soft Tissue Findings Domain

value.value: A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to musculoskeletal findings, connective and soft tissue findings.
An electrocardiographic finding of ST and T wave changes consistent with impaired myocardial perfusion.
A procedure that captures pictures of blood flow throughout the heart muscle.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to nervous system findings.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to nonclinical pregnancy results.
An area outside of that in which an individual lives.

label.value: Non-Sustained Atrial Tachycardia by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of an atrial tachycardia which terminates in less than 30 seconds. (CDISC)

An electrocardiographic finding of an atrial rhythm which originates from the sinoatrial node that is considered normal for the population. There are no extra beats or conduction abnormalities. (CDISC)
Is not an option.

label.value: Observed Volume of Distribution Normalized by Dose

value.value: The volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following intravascular administration, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the dose.

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Anterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V3 and V4, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the anterior wall of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Anterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V3 through V6, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the anterolateral wall of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Anteroseptal Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V1 through V4, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the anteroseptal wall of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Extensive Anterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V1 to V6, I and aVL, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction involving the anterior and anterolateral walls of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate High Lateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads I and aVL, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the high lateral wall of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Inferior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads III, aVF and often II, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the inferior wall of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Lateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V5, V6, I and aVL, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the lateral wall of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Posterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in leads V1 or V2 of an initial R wave duration greater than or equal to 40 ms, R wave greater than S wave, and upright T wave, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the posterior wall of the left ventricle, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. Evidence of inferior or lateral myocardial infarction is usually also present. (CDISC)

label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Right Ventricular Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding, in the presence of an old or age indeterminate inferior wall myocardial infarction, of Q waves greater than or equal to 40 ms in duration in the right ventricular leads V4R through V6R. (CDISC)
